An issue tracking app typically has the following features:

    Ability to create and track issues, such as bugs or tasks
    Assign issues to specific team members
    Set priorities and due dates for issues
    Ability to add comments and updates to issues
    Ability to categorize and filter issues by various attributes, such as status, severity, and project
    Notifications and email updates when issues are updated or changed
    Ability to search and find specific issues
    Ability to attach files and documents to issues
    Ability to integrate with other tools, such as code repositories or project management software
    Ability to generate reports and analytics on issues and project progress
    Ability to customize the workflow and statuses of issues

